# Character Abilities
ABILITY:FEAT|TYPE:NORMAL|CATEGORY:FEAT|KEY:Power Attack|TYPE:GENERAL.FIGHTER.ATTACKOPTION|DESC:On your action, before making attack rolls for a round, you may choose to subtract up to %1 from all melee attack rolls and add the same number to all melee damage rolls.&pipe;PowerAttackMax
ABILITY:FEAT|TYPE:NORMAL|CATEGORY:FEAT|KEY:Exotic Weapon Proficiency|APPLIEDTO:Sword (Bastard)|TYPE:GENERAL.FIGHTER|DESC:Choose a type of exotic weapon. You understand how to use that type of exotic weapon in combat.
ABILITY:FEAT|TYPE:NORMAL|CATEGORY:FEAT|KEY:Endurance|TYPE:GENERAL|DESC:You gain a +4 bonus on checks relating to stamina or extended physical activity. Also, you may sleep in light or medium armor without becoming fatigued.
ABILITY:FEAT|TYPE:NORMAL|CATEGORY:FEAT|KEY:Cleave|TYPE:GENERAL.FIGHTER.ATTACKOPTION|DESC:If you deal a creature enough damage to make it drop, you get an immediate, extra melee attack against another creature within reach. You can use this ability once per round.
ABILITY:FEAT|TYPE:NORMAL|CATEGORY:FEAT|KEY:Great Cleave|TYPE:GENERAL.FIGHTER.ATTACKOPTION|DESC:This feat works like Cleave, except that there is no limit to the number of times you can use it per round.
